7. Exploring IAM
Create a second “Test User” in IAM and assign him the Storage Object Viewer role for a
specific bucket.
Activity 4: Essential Google Cloud Infrastructure: Core Services
Lab: Exploring IAM

✅ PART 1: Start Lab & Login
Click Start Lab
Click Open Google Cloud Console
Login using:
Username 1
Password
Open another tab (Incognito)
→ Login with Username 2

👉 Now you have:

Tab 1 → Username 1 (Admin)
Tab 2 → Username 2 (Test User)
✅ PART 2: Explore IAM
In Username 1 tab:
Go to ☰ Navigation Menu
Click IAM & Admin → IAM
Click Grant Access
Observe available roles (Viewer, Editor, Storage roles, etc.)
Click Cancel
In Username 2 tab:
Go to IAM & Admin → IAM
Notice:
Has Viewer role
Cannot edit permissions ❌
✅ PART 3: Create Storage Bucket
In Username 1 tab:
Go to Cloud Storage → Buckets
Click Create
Enter:
Bucket name → (unique name, e.g. my-bucket-12345)
Location type → Multi-region
Click Create
✅ Upload File
Click Upload → Upload file
Select any file from your system
After upload:
Click ⋮ (3 dots) → Rename
Rename to: sample.txt
✅ Verify Access (Username 2)
Switch to Username 2 tab
Go to Cloud Storage → Buckets
✅ You should see the bucket
❌ PART 4: Remove Project Access
In Username 1 tab:
Go to IAM & Admin → IAM
Find Username 2
Click Remove Access
Click Confirm
Verify (Username 2):
Refresh page
Try opening:
Cloud Storage
❌ You will get permission error
✅ PART 5: Give Storage Object Viewer Role (IMPORTANT)
In Username 1 tab:
Go to IAM & Admin → IAM
Click Grant Access
Enter:
New principal → Username 2 email
Select role:
Cloud Storage → Storage Object Viewer
Click Save
✅ Verify Limited Access (Username 2)
Switch to Username 2 tab
Open Cloud Shell
Run:
gcloud storage ls gs://YOUR_BUCKET_NAME

👉 Output: Bucket contents visible ✅

⚠️ Note:

Cannot see full project
Can only access storage objects
✅ PART 6: Create Service Account
In Username 1 tab:
Go to IAM & Admin → Service Accounts
Click Create Service Account
Enter:
Name → read-bucket-objects
Click Create and Continue
Assign role:
Storage Object Viewer
Click Done
✅ PART 7: Grant Service Account User Role
Click your service account
Click Manage Permissions
Click Grant Access
Enter:
altostrat.com
Role:
Service Accounts → Service Account User
Click Save
✅ PART 8: Give Compute Admin Role
Go to IAM
Click Grant Access
Enter:
altostrat.com
Role:
Compute Engine → Compute Instance Admin (v1)
Click Save
✅ PART 9: Create VM with Service Account
Go to Compute Engine → VM Instances
Click Create Instance

Fill:

Name → demoiam
Machine → e2-micro
OS → Debian 12
Security section:
Service account → read-bucket-objects
Access scope → Set access for each API
Storage → Read/Write

Click Create

✅ PART 10: Test Permissions (VERY IMPORTANT)
SSH into VM:
Click SSH
❌ Try listing instances:
gcloud compute instances list

👉 ERROR → No permission

✅ Download file:
gcloud storage cp gs://YOUR_BUCKET_NAME/sample.txt .
Rename file:
mv sample.txt sample2.txt
❌ Upload (will fail):
gcloud storage cp sample2.txt gs://YOUR_BUCKET_NAME

👉 ERROR → No write permission

✅ PART 11: Fix Permission
In Username 1 tab:
Go to IAM
Find service account
Click Edit
Change role to:
Storage Object Creator
Click Save
✅ PART 12: Retry Upload

Back in SSH:

gcloud storage cp sample2.txt gs://YOUR_BUCKET_NAME

👉 ✅ SUCCESS

🎯 FINAL RESULT

You successfully:
✔ Created Test User
✔ Removed project access
✔ Gave limited Storage access only
✔ Created Service Account
✔ Tested real IAM permissions
✔ Fixed permission issue

💡 Quick Concept (Exam Tip)
Viewer → Read everything
Storage Object Viewer → Read only storage
Storage Object Creator → Upload allowed
IAM controls access 🔐
